sols_latex:
From the matrix,

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc}1 & 2 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \end{array}\right.\left| \begin{array}{c} 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

we see that the third row is all zeros (including the augmented part)
and so one of the variables is a free parameter. From the second row we
see that x\_3=0. Let the free parameter be x\_2. Then from the first row
we see that x\_1=-2x\_2. Therefore we have a null vector,

\begin{align*}
\begin{bmatrix}
-2\\
1\\
0
\end{bmatrix}
\end{align*}

and the solution is

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{x}=t
\begin{bmatrix}
-2\\
1\\
0
\end{bmatrix}.
\end{align*}

There are an infinite number of solutions.

